{{Quote|Widely considered the best soldiers in the galaxy, Imperial spacetroopers specialize in assaulting and capturing enemy starships. Like the Imperial Marines, they serve aboard the vessels of the Imperial Navy. Unlike the Marines, spacetroopers operate best in the airless interstellar void.|[[TX-5532]], ''[[Imperial Handbook: A Commander's Guide]]''|<ref name="Imperial Handbook" />}}
The '''Zero-G assault stormtroopers''', commonly known as '''spacetroopers''', were members of a specialized branch of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Stormtrooper Corps/Legends|Stormtrooper Corps]] equipped and trained to capture enemy [[Starship/Legends|vessels]] intact. They also operated within the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]].

==Equipment==
[[File:SpaceTrooper2.jpg|thumb|left|150px|Light spacetrooper armor.]]

To perform their missions, spacetroopers wore a two-meter tall set of [[Zero-G Assault Stormtrooper Armor Mark I|Zero-G armor]] that interfaced with standard [[Stormtrooper armor/Legends|stormtrooper armor]]. The suit provided a hermetic seal against the vacuum of space and propulsion that allowed spacetroopers to move and fight in space for extended periods. As a result, the official field manual for officers in the [[Imperial Military/Legends|Imperial Military]], ''[[Imperial Handbook: A Commander's Guide]]'', compared it to a small-single pilot spacecraft, with one of the leaders of the Rebel Alliance, [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]], reluctantly admitting that the description was indeed very accurate, citing that a single spacetrooper was more than capable of breaching and seizing control of a blockade runner.<ref name="Imperial Handbook">''[[Star Wars: Imperial Handbook: A Commander's Guide]]''</ref> It is also stated that Space troopers are considered the best troops in the galaxy.

In addition, the suit allowed them to carry heavy firepower, turning each trooper into the equivalent of a light tank. Weapon systems included two shoulder mounted, magazine fed [[Grenade launcher/Legends|grenade launchers]] able to fire [[Concussion grenade/Legends|concussion grenades]], [[Gas grenade/Legends|gas grenades]], and [[Stun grenade/Legends|stun grenades]]; a right gauntlet [[Blaster cannon/Legends|blaster cannon]]; and a left gauntlet miniature [[Proton torpedo/Legends|proton torpedo]] launcher. Each gauntlet also included [[Laser cutter/Legends|laser cutters]] to penetrate ship hulls.<ref name="Rebellion Era Campaign Guide" />

In addition to the large, boxy armor most commonly seen, spacetroopers during the [[Thrawn campaign]] made use of a more form fitting style of armor. This style appeared as a bulkier form of standard stormtrooper armor that afforded greater flexibility but greatly reduced firepower, armor, and mobility. It is unclear if this model of spacetrooper armor replaced the older design or was a variant.

A third style of "Spacetrooper" emerged early, during the building of the first Death Star, but was rarely seen. These units were deployed to many zero-G environments, such as areas outside the Death Star's artificially generated atmosphere. It was simply standard stormtrooper armor vacuum sealed, with a rebreather unit and a back-mounted jetpack. This system had no built-in weapons, and just relied on what the trooper carried in-hand. While it had much less mobility in space, it did have the advantage of being lighter, smaller and easier to move in small spaces, such as inside ships or bases that did not have atmosphere or gravity.

For all their advantages, however, spacetroopers had weaknesses. Like most electronics-based equipment, spacetrooper armor was vulnerable to EMP bursts, which if spacetroopers were caught in a burst, they were effectively left immobile in space. In addition, their weapons systems were ill-suited for [[Starfighter combat/Legends|starfighter combat]].<ref name="Imperial Handbook" />

==History==
[[File:A_New_Hope-_Joe_Johnston_as_Spacetrooper.jpg|thumb|right|250px|Stormtroopers wearing light spacetrooper armor on the first Death Star]]
Originating during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], the [[Galactic Marines/Legends|Galactic Marines]] tested prototype spacetrooper suits during the [[Battle of New Bornalex]]. The weapon systems failed, and the marines were forced to use hand-to-hand combat and succeeded.<ref name="DB-Bacara, Commander">{{DB|character|commanderbacara|Bacara, Commander}}</ref> The Empire corrected the problem with a new armor design by Dr. [[Nashiak Llalik]] (based on Llalik's own scrapped pet project [[Sunder 9]] armor)<ref name="air">''[[Alliance Intelligence Reports]]''</ref> and made use of them.

[[Platoon/Legends|Platoons]] of forty spacetroopers were deployed from [[Gamma-class assault shuttle/Legends|''Gamma''-class assault shuttles]]. Enemy [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]] could be easily overtaken with well organized assaults.

Notable spacetroopers included [[Rom Mohc]], the developer of the [[Dark Trooper/Legends|Dark Trooper]] [[Dark Trooper Project|Project]].

Spacetroopers, along with representatives from every specialized [[Stormtrooper Corps/Legends|Stormtrooper Corps]], were assigned to [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] personal [[Death Squadron/Legends|Death Squadron]].<ref name="GG3">''[[Galaxy Guide 3: The Empire Strikes Back]]''</ref> Spacetroopers were used to patrol the outside of the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|First Death Star]]. Several spacetroopers served in the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], attacking [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] [[Starship/Legends|ships]] entering the [[Death Star II/Legends|Second Death Star]].

Spacetroopers continued to see use after Endor, with Leia requesting that the Rebel forces require training and countermeasures against them. [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]], the leader of [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]], suggested using starfighter escorts due to the spacetroopers being incapable of handling dogfights, and the General [[Crix Madine/Legends|Crix Madine]] likewise suggested implementing EMP measures due to their effecting spacetroopers.<ref name="Imperial Handbook" />

Spacetroopers were deployed during the [[Battle of Sluis Van]] in [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]]. They were primarily used in an attempt to capture a number of [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[capital ship]]s under repair at the [[Sluis Van Shipyards]]. However, [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] and [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]] managed to override the remotely controlled [[Plasma-Jet Mole Miner|mole miners]] that the capture parties had used as [[Boarding craft/Legends|boarding craft]] and activated their drills. This depressurized the ships' bridges, killing the standard [[stormtrooper]]s and sucking the spacetroopers into space, where they were engaged by [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]]. By the end of the battle, seven of the spacetroopers had been destroyed, while the remaining two [[Self-destruct mechanism/Legends|self-destructed]], with one crippling a [[Corvette/Legends|Corvette]] in the process.<ref name="Heir to the Empire">''[[Heir to the Empire]]''</ref>

In [[11 ABY/Legends|11 ABY]], during the [[Battle of the Maw]], two Spacetroopers were sent to the reactor of the [[Death Star prototype]] when the Imperials piloting the [[Battle station/Legends|Battlestation]] detected an intruder, which turned out to be the ''[[Millennium Falcon/Legends|Millennium Falcon]]'', piloted by [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], [[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]], and [[Lando Calrissian/Legends|Lando Calrissian]], who were attempting to sabotage the station by planting explosives. As the Spacetroopers began to scuffle with Jade, one was thrown into the reactor and killed. The other attempted to disable the explosives as the Falcon flew away, disarming all but one, which exploded, killing him. Eventually, several more Spacetroopers were sent to repair the reactor, understanding that the radiation was lethal and that they would likely not survive. They managed to successfully make their repairs before succumbing to the lethal doses of radiation.<ref name="CotF" />

==Behind the scenes==
The [[Hasbro]] 2009 version of the Spacetrooper (Hasbro's 2nd Spacetrooper toy, the first based on the Light Spacetrooper armor above) looks like an ordinary [[Stormtrooper/Legends|Stormtrooper]] but with jetpack and attachable breathing apparatus. He is armed with [[E-11 blaster rifle/Legends|E-11 blaster rifle]] and a weapon which resembles a grenade launcher from the [[Battlefront|''Battlefront'' series]]. Production photos from [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']] reveal that effects-designer [[Joe Johnston]] was the man behind the mask, leading to speculation from fans that the Hasbro 2009 figure would feature Johnston. Hasbro stated in a June 2008 Q&A that although they could never do Johnston's likeness on the Spacetrooper figure, they seemed to joke that there could be a "coincidental resemblance."<ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.galactichunter.com/absolutenm/templates/full_article_template_1.asp?articleid=7293&zoneid=2|text=Galactic Hunter - Q&A 2.11|archivedate=20080626113401}}</ref><ref>{{WebCite|url=http://www.oafe.net/monkey/sw4sptr.php|text=OAFE - Star Wars: Spacetrooper review|archivedate=20090304080747}}</ref>
